column10: School dismissal time and tons of kids walking home but multiple drivers fail to yield. Request stronger enforcement at this signal.

This crossing on Beulah Rd adjacent to Abbotsford Dr, southbound traffic has stopped so I crossed with my 5yo and had a frighteningly near miss with a car speeding and failing to yield in the northbound lane
Student biking home from school nearly hit by car in crosswalk/bike lane.

Driver heading southbound on Beulah had to brake heavily to avoid hitting pedestrian on cross walk due to sun in his eyes. Driver apologized but explained he couldn't see us due to the sun obstructing his vision.
Drivers routinely drive through this crosswalk even with pedestrians halfway across the street.  It's a very dangerous spot.
